<TITLE> Hasina to see public on Saturdays </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 7 (bdnews24.com) - Prime minister Sheikh Hasina will meet with her party leaders and activists and members of the public on Saturdays, her press secretary has said. "The prime minister has set aside a weekly time to meet with party supporters and general members of the public, at her political office in Dhanmondi, on Saturday evenings," the PM's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad said. Party leaders and activists from different districts and Upazila, and professionals met with the PM Saturday evening. Members of Gopalganj unit of Bangladesh Muktijoddah Sangsad, Kotalipara Baptists Christian Association and the National Church Council also met with the PM, said Azad. Hasina heard various issues from the freedom fighters and assured they would be addressed, he said. The Christian community called on Hasina to update the Christian Marriage Act 1872. The prime minister promised to give it attention, said the press secretary. bdnews
